    faqTitle: 'Common Questions',
    faqSub: 'Everything you need to know about how ZeroGEX works and how to get the most from it.',
    faq1Q: 'What is Gamma Exposure (GEX) and why does it matter?',
    faq1A: "Gamma Exposure is the aggregate sensitivity of options dealers' delta hedges to price moves in the underlying. When dealers are long gamma (positive net GEX at spot), they must sell when price rises and buy when it falls — creating a dampening effect on volatility and strong intraday support/resistance. When they're short gamma (negative net GEX at spot), they chase price and amplify moves in both directions. Knowing the GEX regime helps you understand whether the market is likely to mean-revert or trend on any given day.",
